cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of detecting and tracking fibers in microscopic images of materials. This problem is related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image processing and object detection. The proposed method uses unsupervised learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.MM) and specifically in deep learning (cs.LG). The method also involves using priors and spatio-temporal consistency, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for improving the accuracy of models. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of detecting and tracking objects in images, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) for tasks such as image search and object recognition.
